  The recovery manager uses ARIES (Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability) to ensure atomicity by ensuring that all transactions are executed in a consistent and isolated manner, and that the database remains consistent even in the event of system failures. ARIES ensures that transactions are executed in the order they were started, and that the database remains consistent even if some transactions are rolled back. This is achieved by maintaining a set of transaction logs that record the state of the database before and after each transaction, and by using these logs to roll back transactions that fail. The recovery manager also ensures that the database remains consistent even if some transactions are committed, by using the transaction logs to restore the database to its consistent state after a failure.
