  📝 Retrieved Answer:
  ----------------------------------------------------------
  The goals of Online Transaction Processing (OLTP) and data analytics are fundamentally different. OLTP is designed to handle high-volume, real-time transactions, ensuring that the system can process and respond to transactions quickly and efficiently. It aims to minimize latency and maximize throughput, ensuring that users can interact with the system without delay.
  
  On the other hand, data analytics focuses on extracting insights and patterns from large datasets, often using historical data to predict future trends or behaviors. Data analytics is typically used for decision-making, forecasting, and understanding customer behavior. It involves complex data analysis techniques, such as machine learning and statistical modeling, to uncover meaningful information from data.
  
  In summary, while OLTP is focused on real-time transaction processing, data analytics is concerned with extracting insights from historical data to inform decision-making.
  ----------------------------------------------------------

